### Generics Basics

Generics enable type-safe code that works with multiple types. They parameterize types with type arguments.

```dart
void main() {
  List<String> names = ['Alice', 'Bob'];
  Map<String, int> ages = {'Alice': 30, 'Bob': 25};
  Set<int> numbers = {1, 2, 3};
}
```

### Generic Functions

```dart
T first<T>(List<T> items) {
  return items[0];
}

void main() {
  print(first<int>([1, 2, 3])); // 1
  print(first<String>(['a', 'b'])); // 'a'
  // Type inference works too:
  print(first([1, 2, 3])); // 1 (int inferred)
}
```

### Generic Classes

```dart
class Box<T> {
  T value;

  Box(this.value);

  T getValue() => value;

  void setValue(T newValue) {
    value = newValue;
  }
}

void main() {
  var intBox = Box<int>(42);
  print(intBox.getValue()); // 42

  var stringBox = Box<String>('Hello');
  print(stringBox.getValue()); // Hello
}
```

### Multiple Type Parameters

```dart
class Pair<K, V> {
  K key;
  V value;

  Pair(this.key, this.value);

  @override
  String toString() => '$key: $value';
}

void main() {
  var pair = Pair<String, int>('age', 30);
  print(pair); // age: 30
}
```

### Generic Constraints

Use `extends` to constrain type parameters.

```dart
class Repository<T extends Entity> {
  final List<T> _items = [];

  void add(T item) => _items.add(item);
  T? findById(int id) => _items.where((e) => e.id == id).firstOrNull;
}

class Entity {
  final int id;
  Entity(this.id);
}

class User extends Entity {
  String name;
  User(int id, this.name) : super(id);
}
```

| Concept | Syntax | Description |
|---------|--------|-------------|
| Generic class | `class Name<T>` | Class parameterized by type |
| Generic function | `T fn<T>(T val)` | Function parameterized by type |
| Type constraint | `<T extends Base>` | T must be subtype of Base |
| Multiple params | `<K, V>` | Multiple type parameters |

> **Key Point:** Generics provide compile-time type safety without runtime overhead. Use them to build reusable components that work with any type.

codeExample:
class Stack<T> {
  final List<T> _items = [];

  void push(T item) => _items.add(item);
  T pop() => _items.removeLast();
  T get peek => _items.last;
  bool get isEmpty => _items.isEmpty;
  int get length => _items.length;
}

void main() {
  var numberStack = Stack<int>();
  numberStack.push(1);
  numberStack.push(2);
  numberStack.push(3);

  print(numberStack.pop()); // 3
  print(numberStack.pop()); // 2
  print(numberStack.peek);  // 1

  var stringStack = Stack<String>();
  stringStack.push('a');
  stringStack.push('b');
  print(stringStack.pop()); // b
}
